NOTE ON DATA AND SCOPE:

This MIT License applies to the **source code** in this repository.

The CSI (Culture-Specific Item) taxonomy, schema, annotation guidelines, and
released data artifacts (gold annotations, BIO datasets, lexicons, test set
with CSI tags) are released under the **Creative Commons Attribution 4.0
International License (CC-BY 4.0)**. If you use these artifacts in your own
work, please cite the accompanying paper (see `CITATION.cff`).

The Persian text and English translations used in this work are publicly
available materials (Nicholson's English translation of the Masnavi is in
the public domain since 2015). This repository does not redistribute the
full parallel corpus; only the test split with CSI annotations is included
to support the evaluation methodology (see `data/README.md`).

Audio-based components of the original research are not part of this
repository. The full thesis (Ansari, 2026, UQAM) describes multimodal
extensions which are outside the scope of this code release.
